<h1 id="add-file-in-existing-archive">Add File in Existing Archive</h1>
<p>While managing archives with tar,Â  there might also be a case to add a new file in the existing archive. For that, we use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">-r</code> options. Syntax <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tar -rvfÂ Â Archive-file-name.tarÂ  /path-of/file-you-want-to-add-to-the-archive</code>.</p>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alon</span><span class="vi">@localhost</span> <span class="o">~</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="err">$</span> <span class="n">tar</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">rvf</span> <span class="n">myFiles</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nf">tar</span> <span class="sr">/etc/</span><span class="n">hosts</span>
<span class="sr">/etc/</span><span class="n">hosts</span></code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="update-existing-archive">Update Existing Archive</h1>

<p>To update current existing archive file, we can use the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">-u</code> options. Syntax <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tar -uvf  Archive-file-name.tar </code></p>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">alon</span><span class="vi">@localhost</span> <span class="o">~</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="err">$</span> <span class="n">tar</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">uvf</span> <span class="n">myFiles</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nf">tar</span></code></pre></figure>

<h1 id="monitoring-archive">Monitoring Archive</h1>

<p>You can also view all the files for the archive before extracting. For that, use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">-t</code> option. Sytntax <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tar -tvf  Archive-file-name.tar </code></p>

